===Alternative forms===
* [[aard-vark]], [[erdvark]]

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|af|en}} {{term|aardvark|lang=af}} (obsolete), {{term|erdvark|lang=af}}, from {{etyl|af|en}} {{term|aarde||earth|lang=af}}, (from {{etyl|nl|en}}, from {{etyl|dum|en}} {{term|aerde|lang=dum}}) + {{etyl|af|en}} {{term|vark||pig|lang=af}}, (from {{etyl|dum|en}} {{term|varken||pig|lang=dum}}).Early European colonists in South Africa noticed that the animal was similar to a pig, while "aarde" hints at the animal's habit of burrowing.

===Pronunciation===
{{wikisource1911Enc|Aard-vark}}
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/ˈɑːd.vɑːk/|lang=en}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈɑɹdˌvɑɹk/|/ˈɑd.vɑk/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The [[nocturnal]], [[insectivorous]], burrowing, [[mammal]] ''[[Orycteropus afer]]'', of the order [[Tubulidentata]], somewhat resembling a [[pig]], common in some parts of sub-Saharan Africa. {{defdate|First attested in the late 18<sup>th</sup> c.}}
#: ''The '''aardvark''' burrows in the ground and feeds mostly on termites, which it catches with its long, slimy tongue.''
# {{context|slang|particularly in the southeast|_|US|lang=en}} A [[silly]] or [[credulous]] person who is prone to [[mistakes]] or [[blunders]].
#: ''I walked into the wrong bathroom like a total '''aardvark'''.''

